Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Pop both veg onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf until soft, ~{15-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the veg roasts, add the @linguine{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back into the #saucepan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use #scissors if easier).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{180%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Stir in the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%can}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @sugar{1} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once everything's cooked, combine the roasted veg, cooked pasta and sauce in whichever pan is the largest.

Stir in half the chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Add a splash of @water{} if it looks a little dry.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, serve your roasted pepper and aubergine linguine in #bowls{}.

Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining chives and cheese. Enjoy!